{"name":"http-livereload-cli","description":"Connect based http server with livereload for the command line.","version":"0.1.3","license":"MIT","repository":"https://github.com/tarsolya/http-livereload-cli","keywords":["http","livereload","cli","watch","make"],"main":"./bin/http-livereload","dependencies":{"connect":"^3.4.0","connect-livereload":"^0.5.3","exec-sh":"^0.2.0","morgan":"^1.6.0","optimist":"*","sane":"^1.1.3","serve-static":"^1.10.0","tiny-lr-fork":"latest"},"bin":{"http-livereload":"./bin/http-livereload","livereload-notify":"./bin/livereload-notify"},"gitHead":"e22a14528aeee6a612998b490e7358969ef3336b","homepage":"https://github.com/tarsolya/http-livereload-cli#readme","scripts":{},"versions":[{"number":"0.1.0","date":"2015-07-04T20:47:08.810Z"},{"number":"0.1.1","date":"2015-07-09T22:07:25.219Z"},{"number":"0.1.2","date":"2015-07-28T06:15:39.307Z"},{"number":"0.1.3","date":"2015-07-28T06:21:42.749Z"}],"readme":"http-livereload\n==========\n\nCLI wrapper for starting a http server with integrated LiveReload and file change watcher / notifier.\n\nUsage\n-----\nRun `http-livereload` without arguments for options.\n\nExample\n-----\n```\nhttp-livereload ./www --watch-dir ./src --watch-cmd='make reload' --cordova\n```\n\nServe `www` on `localhost:3000` with _Cordova_ device stub and watch for changes in `src`.\nExecutes `make reload` on changes.\n\nLicense\n-------\nReleased under permissive MIT License.\n","created":"2015-07-04T20:47:08.810Z","modified":"2015-07-28T06:21:42.749Z","lastPublisher":{"name":"tarsolya","email":"tarsolya@gmail.com"},"owners":[{"name":"tarsolya","email":"tarsolya@gmail.com"}],"other":{"_attachments":{},"_from":".","_id":"http-livereload-cli","_nodeVersion":"2.3.4","_npmUser":{"name":"tarsolya","email":"tarsolya@gmail.com"},"_npmVersion":"2.12.1","_rev":"1-332ef8e7a457c4ea0400ad845731d260","_shasum":"6d4d241725f9ad2262fde669e2215fa4d4e70e42","author":{"name":"Andr√°s Tarsoly","email":"tarsolya@gmail.com"},"bugs":{"url":"https://g